Task 3: CSS Selectors
Selectors allow targeting of HTML elements:

- Element Selector targets all instances of a tag: p { color: red; }
- Class Selector applies to elements with a specific class: .myClass { color: green; }
- ID Selector targets a unique element: #myId { font-weight: bold; }
- Attribute Selector matches elements with an attribute: [type="text"] { border: 1px solid; }
- Pseudo-Class Selector targets elements in specific states: a:hover { color: orange; }